race.comment: CHICAGO STORM (1) was held up until late last start on the Parks track but once clear he really savaged the line. Has come back in career-best form this campaign and only needs to maintain that level to go very close again. SIR NOW (7) left himself far too much to do behind CHICAGO STORM last time but charged late. Meets several of these much better at the weights and reunites with Collett, who has an excellent record aboard. Freshened with five weeks between runs and sharpened by a trial win. Can bounce back to winning form. GRINZINGER PRINCE (5) was dominant first-up here and then only warmed late at Caulfield. Kept fresh with six weeks between runs and tuned up with a jumpout. Ready to launch and no surprise to see him in the finish. WATCHME WIN (2) drops in grade and boasts a terrific record at this track. A G3 winner who oozes class, he just has to shoulder the big weight but remains a genuine chance. PRAIRIE FLOWER (4) Hasn't won for a little while but loves it here. Safely kept.
